Newly crowned Miss Universe 2019 South Africa's Zozibini Tunzi poses during a press conference after the 2019 Miss Universe pageant at the Tyler Perry Studios in Atlanta, Georgia on December 8, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's beauty queen, Zozibini Tunzi, has been crowned Miss Universe 2019. READ: Zozibini Tunzi crowned 2019 Miss Universe The Eastern Cape beauty took the title at the pageant held in Atlanta in the US on Sunday, 08 December. Zozibini is the third South African to win the Miss Universe crown following Margaret Gardiner's win in 1978 and Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters in 2017. Miss Universe 2019 Zozibini Tunzi, of South Africa, before departing for Atlanta, Georgia for the beauty pageant. Miss Indonesia Frederika Cull, Miss Nepal Pradeepta Adhikari,Miss South Africa Zozibini Tunzi, and Miss India Vartika Singh pose with cast members of Volta during Volta By Cirque Du Soleil at Atlantic Station on December 04, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. Miss Universe contestants pose for a picture ahead of the pageant on Sunday. Miss South Africa Zozibini Tunzi revealed her national costume ahead of the Miss Universe pageant. Miss South Africa Zozibini Tunzi competes in the swimsuit competition during the 2019 Miss Universe Pageant at Tyler Perry Studios on December 08, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. Miss South Africa Zozibini Tunzi appears onstage at the 2019 Miss Universe Pageant at Tyler Perry Studios on December 08, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. Steve Harvey and Miss South Africa Zozibini Tunzi speak onstage at the 2019 Miss Universe Pageant at Tyler Perry Studios on December 08, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. Miss Puerto Rico Madison Anderson, Miss South Africa Zozibini Tunzi, Miss Mexico Sofía Aragón appear onstage at the 2019 Miss Universe Pageant at Tyler Perry Studios on December 08, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. Miss Universe 2019 Zozibini Tunzi, of South Africa, just before she is crowned onstage at the 2019 Miss Universe Pageant at Tyler Perry Studios on December 08, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. Miss Universe 2018 Philippines' Catriona Gray (R) crowns the new Miss Universe 2019 South Africa's Zozibini Tunzi on stage during the 2019 Miss Universe pageant at the Tyler Perry Studios in Atlanta, Georgia on December 8, 2019. File: Newly crowned Miss Universe 2019 South Africa's Zozibini Tunzi waves from the stage after the 2019 Miss Universe pageant at the Tyler Perry Studios in Atlanta, Georgia on December 8, 2019. Miss Universe 2019 Zozibini Tunzi, of South Africa, appears at a press conference following the 2019 Miss Universe Pageant at Tyler Perry Studios on December 08, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. Newly crowned Miss Universe 2019 South Africa's Zozibini Tunzi poses during a press conference after the 2019 Miss Universe pageant at the Tyler Perry Studios in Atlanta, Georgia on December 8, 2019.